festival.introText:
Land Beyond are proud to announce the Stage Hosts for Brighton's first-ever electronic music festival with camping.

 

World renowned brands such as DNB All Stars, CruCast, LOCUS! Disco Disco, Mixtape Madness, Grime Originals and more will host a mouth-watering line-up of international talent.

 

Land Beyond Festival

The Lost World

April 28th - 30th 2023

Waterhall, Brighton

faqs.question: Is there camping available at Land Beyond Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes, there are various camping options available for Land Beyond Festival including VIP options.

faqs.question: When isLand Beyond Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Land Beyond will take place on Saturday 28th and Sunday 29th of May 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Land Beyond Festival?
faqs.answer:
Waterhall Playing Fields, Brighton (BN1 8YR) 

Land Beyond has no parking facilities available on site, or in the surrounding area; do not attempt to park your car illegally. We are a green-friendly event!

Shuttle bus: details tbc.

At the end of the event, shuttle buses will operate from 9pm-end of the event, taking people back to Old Steine, Brighton.

Taxis: drop off and pick up from Waterhall.

You are able to walk to and from Land Beyond, but please be mindful of local traffic and use the designated paths.

 

We are next to an extremely busy roundabout. Please ensure you leave enough time to make your last train out of Brighton as there will be no additional late-night services.

faqs.question: Is there disabled access at Land Beyond?
faqs.answer:
This event features disabled parking, disabled access and a viewing platform.

Carer/Personal Assistant tickets for those wishing to accompany a paying customer are available for this event, subject to providing any of the following documentation -

 

*The front page of DLA letter with PIP letter 

*The front page of Attendance Allowance letter 

*Evidence of being registered as severely sight impaired (blind) 

*Recognised Assistance Dog ID card 

*Valid Access Card showing you require a +1 to accompany you

 

 

If this applies to you then please contact the Skiddle Customer Care team with your documentation and order ID by submitting a support request here: https://help.skiddle.com/hc/en-us/requests/new

faqs.question: How much are Land BeyondFestival tickets?
faqs.answer: Please see the tickets section for more info.

faqs.question: What is included in a Weekend Camping ticket?
faqs.answer: Weekend Camping includes access to the campsite and festival for 3 days.

faqs.question: Where is Land Beyond Festival?
faqs.answer: Land Beyond is located at Waterhall, Brighton.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: There are no payment plan tickets currently available.

faqs.question: What is included in a VIP Weekend Camping ticket?
faqs.answer: VIP Weekend Camping includes access to the campsite and festival for 3 days plus access to the VIP area inside the arena.

faqs.question: Does Land BeyondFestival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: You must be 18 or older to attend Land Beyond. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: What is included in a Weekend Glamping ticket?
faqs.answer: Weekend Glamping includes a fully furnished bell tent (for 2, 3 or 4 people) plus access to a separately managed campsite with posh loos, posh showers, and a dedicated entrance lane to the main arena.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Land Beyond Festival?
faqs.answer: You are not permitted to bring your own food or drinks into the festival.
